9 Subject: Executive; retirement; Vermont State Employees’ Retirement System
10 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to amend the
11 membership, normal retirement allowance, and contribution rates for Group G
12 in the Vermont State Employees’ Retirement System. This bill also proposes
13 to allow a member of the State Employees’ Retirement System to earn
14 creditable service for employment in a temporary or seasonal position with the
15 State and expands the circumstances where a member may receive creditable
16 service for prior military service without the need to make contributions. In
17 addition, this bill proposes to create a statutory contractual right for members
18 of the State Employees’ Retirement System.
